A Nigerian Application Programming Interface (API) and finance start-up, OnePipe has partnered with Fidelity Bank to launch PayGatePlus to accelerate online payments. PayGate is the bank’s flagship online payment platform but it partnered with OnePipe to move to the PayGatePlus platform. ‘Why Buhari should assent to mental health bill’ I want to succeed Ganduje, Kano SSG declares According to the Chief Executive Officer (CEO) and Founder of OnePipe, Ope Adeoye explained that his company seeks to help businesses and partners achieve maximum operational excellence, deeper customer intimacy and ultimately revenue growth. He further explained that PayGatePlus provides merchants with the rails to deliver diverse financial services to their customers across a range of platforms such as; websites, mobile apps, social media and in-store in the case of retail outlets. Also, Executive Director and Chief Operations and Information Officer of Fidelity Bank, Stanley Amuchie, described innovation as the key pillar of the bank’s strategic framework; saying, the solution aims to enable businesses across different sectors to easily integrate financial services with their product offerings.